Ms Bridi made the pledge during her official field visit to some… MAUREEN ODUNGA 29 JANUARY 2017 SOURCE: DAILY NEWS WORLD Bank (WB), Director for External Communications and partnerships, Ms Haleh Bridi have reiterated their commitment on encouraging more development partners to support the Tanzania Social Action Fund (TASAF) programmes to enroll unreached poor households. Ms Bridi made the pledge during her official field visit to some of the TASAF productive social safety net programme (PSSN) at Kondo Village in Bagamoyo District on Friday.

“We will continue to encourage other partners to join forces in funding the programme so that more poor people are covered,” said Ms Bridi.

